@startuml PyData Copilot — Part 1: Prompt Intake & Context Retrieval

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #2C3E50
    LifeLineBorderColor #95A5A6
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #ECF0F1
    ParticipantBorderColor #2980B9
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #D6EAF8
    ParticipantFontColor #1A252F
    ParticipantFontStyle bold
    ActorBorderColor #27AE60
    ActorBackgroundColor #D5F5E3
    ActorFontColor #1A252F
    NoteBackgroundColor #FDFEFE
    NoteBorderColor #BDC3C7
    NoteFontColor #2C3E50
    BoxBackgroundColor #F2F3F4
    BoxBorderColor #BDC3C7
    DividerBackgroundColor #D6DBDF
    DividerFontColor #2C3E50
}
skinparam ArrowFontColor #2C3E50
skinparam defaultFontColor #2C3E50
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam ParticipantPadding 10

title <size:14><b>PyData Copilot — Part 1 of 3</b></size>\nPrompt Intake, Memory Retrieval & Intent Classification

actor User as U #D5F5E3
participant "Streamlit UI\n(streamlit_app.py)" as ST #D6EAF8
participant "Turn Pipeline\n(turn.py)" as TP #FDEBD0
participant "Memory Store\n(memory_store.py)" as MS #E8DAEF
participant "Embedding Model\n(nomic-embed-text\nGPU)" as EM #D5F5E3
participant "Intent Classifier\n(user_intent.py)" as IC #FAD7A0

== User Submits Prompt ==

U -> ST : Natural language prompt\nvia st.chat_input
activate ST #D6EAF8

ST -> ST : Append user message\nto pydc.messages
ST -> ST : Render user bubble\n(st.chat_message)
ST -> ST : Initialize progress bar\n+ status label container

note right of ST
  Pipeline steps execute
  sequentially. Progress bar
  updates between each step.
end note

== Step 1 of 5 — Memory Retrieval ==

ST -> TP : get_relevant_memories(ctx)\ncalled via steps pipeline
activate TP #FDEBD0

TP -> MS : get_relevant_memories(\n  query = prompt,\n  limit = 3,\n  score_threshold = 0.52\n)
activate MS #E8DAEF

MS -> MS : _trim_namespace(max=5)\nEvict oldest memories if over limit

MS -> EM : embed_query(prompt)
activate EM #D5F5E3
note right of EM
  Produces a 768-dimensional
  vector representing the
  semantic meaning of
  the user's prompt.
end note
EM --> MS : query_embedding [float x 768]
deactivate EM

MS -> MS : InMemoryStore.search(\n  namespace = (session, id, memories),\n  query = query_embedding\n)

note right of MS
  Cosine similarity computed
  between query vector and all
  stored memory embeddings.
  Items below score 0.52
  are filtered out.
end note

MS --> TP : List[Dict] — matched memories\n(past exchanges + dataset summaries)
deactivate MS

TP --> ST : ctx["memories"] updated
deactivate TP

ST -> ST : progress.progress(20%)
ST -> ST : status.text("Classifying intent…")

== Step 2 of 5 — Intent Classification ==

ST -> TP : classify_intent(ctx)
activate TP #FDEBD0

TP -> IC : classify_intent(\n  user_text = prompt,\n  pydc = session_state\n)
activate IC #FAD7A0

IC -> IC : Casefold prompt text

alt NEW_KEYWORDS detected\n("create", "start", "new plot", "reset"…)
    IC -> IC : return NEW_USER_INTENT
else EDIT_KEYWORDS detected\n("add", "modify", "adjust", "also"…)
    IC -> IC : return EDIT_USER_INTENT
else No keyword match
    IC -> IC : Heuristic fallback:\nif pydc.table or pydc.figure exists\n→ EDIT_USER_INTENT\nelse → NEW_USER_INTENT
end

IC --> TP : intent: str\n(constants.NEW_USER_INTENT or\n constants.EDIT_USER_INTENT)
deactivate IC

TP --> ST : ctx["user_intent"] updated
deactivate TP

ST -> ST : progress.progress(35%)

note over ST, IC
  **Continues in Part 2:** Prompt Construction → LLM Inference → Code Execution → Result Rendering
end note

deactivate ST

@enduml
